p: Sesquiterpenes (bicyclic, tricyclic, monocyclic, and bicyclic sesquiterpenoids) ranged from 19.6% (in the 5–10 min DT fraction) to 3.6% (in the 60–90 min DT fraction). The main EO constituents belonging to the sesquiterpenes are presented in Table 5. β-Caryophyllene, α-caryophyllene, and manoyl oxide were in higher concentrations in the earlier DT fractions compared with the later ones. δ-Cadinene, tau-cadinol, and tau-muurolol had higher concentrations in the 10–30 min DT fraction and they were not found in the 30–60 and 60–90 min DT fractions ( Table 5).
